articles.title: Canned seafood moves beyond tuna sandwiches in a pandemic trend that stuck - New York Post
articles.description: The country’s canned seafood industry is moving well beyond tuna sandwiches, a pandemic-era trend that began with Americans in lockdown demanding more of their cupboard staples.
articles.content:
Sardines swirling in preserved lemons.
